</div>
</div>
<p>The red-throated pipit has a very large range and the global population has been estimated to be about two million individuals. It is rated as being of "<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Least_concern" title="Least concern">least concern</a>" by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IUCN" title="IUCN" class="mw-redirect">IUCN</a> as its population is believed to be stable and it faces no particular threats.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="Anthus_cervinus#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p><br /></p>
